(f) (g) Except as provided by law, a public agency may not adopt a
rule or procedure that creates an exception from disclosure under this
section based upon whether a public record is stored or accessed using
paper, electronic media, magnetic media, optical media, or other
information storage technology.
(g) (h) Except as provided by law, a public agency may not adopt a
rule or procedure nor impose any costs or liabilities that impede or
restrict the reproduction or dissemination of any public record.
(h) (i) Notwithstanding subsection (d) and section 7 of this chapter:
(1) public records subject to IC 5-15 may be destroyed only in
accordance with record retention schedules under IC 5-15; or
(2) public records not subject to IC 5-15 may be destroyed in the
ordinary course of business.".
